00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,720
{\an8}Dad!

2
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,840
{\an8}Who are you? What are you doing here?

3
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,840
{\an8}<i>I have to get into 3C.</i>

4
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,880
{\an8}No matter who tries to stop me.

5
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,760
INCOMING CALL - AIKO

6
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:19,480
I can't read their name.

7
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,600
The assistant at your father's boutique
in Japan called.

8
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:51,280
Cosmic Central wants you
to design their clothes.

9
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,680
It's all thanks to me.

10
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:04,440
Those photos I uploaded of you

11
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,880
are so cool that whoever sees it

12
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,280
can't help but fall in love.

13
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:14,960
I also uploaded them to show
that you're here on vacation in Bangkok,

14
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,600
so, of course, they'd want to see you.

15
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,800
Go. Go ahead.

16
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,400
Now Cosmic Central

17
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,760
has paved the way
for you to walk right in.

18
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:22,200
It's an honor to have you here
at Cosmic Central, Mr. Taiga.

19
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:36,840
I don't visit Thailand much,
but I know your company is number one.

20
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:40,440
Thank you so much
for considering the Kenji brand.

21
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,640
Pardon me.

22
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,600
He's just a designer.

23
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,440
Does he really need a grand welcome
from me downstairs, Atinuch?

24
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,400
It was Ms. Nun's idea, sir.

25
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,960
Actually, this designer's quite special.

26
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,920
His brand is very popular.

27
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,720
If he agrees to design our uniform,

28
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,280
there'll be hashtags,

29
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:22,040
the internet will praise us,
and we'll get hit tweets globally.

30
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,480
I'm busy.

31
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,560
Let whoever's in charge
of the project handle it.

32
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,400
THE PRESIDENT IS NOT GOING

33
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,960
Mr. Taiga,

34
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:23,000
my father's talking to a CEO from Europe.

35
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,560
Let's just start talking.

36
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:31,720
I'm the one who wanted to work
with a leading brand like Kenji anyway.

37
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:47,200
Thank you for working so hard
for our company.

38
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,320
This is to show my gratitude, Rin.

39
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,840
I like people who are straightforward.

40
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,400
On the day of the fire,
I saw your bravery.

41
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:05,320
From now on, no more traffic control work.
Report to the office upstairs.

42
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:26,480
What is it? Go ahead.

43
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:35,440
I'd like to take a picture with you.
It'd be an honor.

44
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,640
One, two, three.

45
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,000
Smile, please.

46
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:21,200
3C Group…

47
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,800
Let's see how I can crush you.

48
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,000
The news about the fire alone

49
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,840
shouldn't have decreased
our stock with 3C-coin this badly.

50
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:55,920
Did you check if there's a team of IOs
spreading fake news, Techut?

51
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:02,520
Don't worry about it, Dad.

52
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:05,480
We just need a team of bots
to pump and dump.

53
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,800
Let's just do a wash trade,
then it'll go back up.

54
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,960
I'll pass. I'm busy with our rebranding.

55
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,760
If you can't do anything to grow my money,

56
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,480
don't ever come see me again.

57
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,520
You've agreed to work with Cosmic Central.

58
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,560
How come you look so unhappy?

59
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,160
I didn't get to meet who I wanted to.

60
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,320
The president,

61
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,600
Naruban.

62
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,120
One of the three co-founders.

63
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:39,080
But the names of the other two
have been removed, vanished like ghosts.

64
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:43,120
Mr. Naruban's the only
major shareholder now.

65
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:49,160
You're designing their uniform.
You'll get to see him eventually.

66
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,920
My design will take a while,

67
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,000
not just a month or two.

68
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,440
Maybe six months if I'm lucky.

69
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,400
I can't wait that long.

70
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:10,320
Just the usual, please.

71
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,240
Sorry.

72
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,760
Do you need some company?

73
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,240
You look pretty stressed.

74
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,960
I'm just stressed about work.

75
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:49,440
I traded 3C-coins
and got only a few million baht.

76
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,760
I was thinking about
buying a private island.

77
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,280
Sounds great.

78
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,560
Where's the island?

79
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,240
My dad loves Thailand.

80
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,480
I'd love to visit sometime.

81
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:09,960
I own a resort near the island.

82
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:14,760
If you're interested, I'll have
my driver take you tomorrow.

83
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,960
Or we can go together tonight.

84
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,680
One glass, please.

85
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,120
I'm so sorry!

86
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,880
Sorry.

87
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,000
I'm so drunk.

88
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,280
Sorry, I need to use the restroom.

89
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,600
Oh?

90
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,800
I'm so sorry.

91
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:06,440
Anyway, I hope you get some tonight.

92
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:08,000
See ya.

93
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:33,920
What's up?

94
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:36,880
Looking for a bad boy tonight, huh?

95
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,440
My body, my choice.

96
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,240
You must not know
who you're flirting with.

97
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,840
Back off before I call the cops.

98
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:57,040
Before they come,
you'll be in pieces, with nothing left.

99
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,040
And maybe

100
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:02,040
you'll get a leaked live video
for your profile.

101
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:11,560
Run while you still can.

102
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,320
That rich handsome guy's got a crazy past.

103
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:17,440
He's assaulted women countless times.

104
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:20,480
If his dad weren't rich,
he would've spent many nights in jail.

105
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,440
What?

106
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:57,080
The lady said she's going home early, sir.

107
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,840
Naruban's eldest son is a total playboy.

108
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:34,560
Let's have some fun, okay?

109
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,040
That's my reward.

110
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:58,040
Cosmic Central is a front for Fire Phoenix
to launder money.

111
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,360
Fire Phoenix.

112
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:04,720
One of the top five secret organizations
wanted by Interpol.

113
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,760
I'll kill their members one by one

114
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,160
until I reach their ringleader,

115
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,079
Damon.

116
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,839
I know

117
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:28,040
that it's wrong,

118
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,720
but for me,

119
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,400
you are the only exception.

120
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,760
I'll help you.

121
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,320
Hello, Mr. Taiga.

122
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,440
Hello.

123
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,520
My driver has food poisoning,

124
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,400
so she's his substitute.

125
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,040
What's your name again?

126
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:31,720
It's Rin, ma'am.

127
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,760
So Rin's his substitute.

128
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,520
3C-coin's taken a nosedive,

129
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,840
yet your sister's going to the beach.

130
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:46,520
She's just crazy over her guy.

131
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:50,240
That designer guy is clever.

132
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:53,400
Nun's desperate.
He only has to please her a little

133
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,360
for her to give her body.

134
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,760
Don't worry, Dad.

135
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:07,080
I'll make sure both our stock
and 3C-coin will skyrocket!

136
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,160
How will you do that?

137
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:17,000
News, of course.
If they used it to manipulate the price,

138
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,200
we can use it too.

139
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:21,000
Those stupid investors love bagholding.

140
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,360
They consume the news for food anyway.

141
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,080
Where's Taiga?

142
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,440
Use your phone.

143
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,920
I called him. He wouldn't pick up.

144
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:51,960
Well, don't call him so often.

145
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:54,240
Men can get annoyed sometimes.

146
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:02,240
You're rich, you're pretty,
but your personality's not it.

147
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,840
Careful, or you'll stay single, madam.

148
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:07,120
Finding a guy is no trouble for me.

149
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,560
However,

150
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,880
you crashing at somebody else's place
like this

151
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,640
speaks volumes about your manners.

152
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,960
I'm only here because Taiga wants me here.

153
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:19,080
I'm here to do my job.

154
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:22,000
A job that someone
with a bubble brain like you…

155
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,640
can never understand.

156
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:32,400
Taiga's off to work.
Everybody's got a job,

157
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,800
except you.

158
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,920
Whenever you're free
and tired of living off your dad,

159
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,520
you should find something to do.
Try to look employed.

160
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,400
Then people might stop
posting with that caption,

161
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,960
"Pretty but dumb."

162
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:57,200
Learn to shut up sometimes.

163
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,680
Got it?

164
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:05,920
Wait! Madam!

165
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,320
Come take care of me!

166
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,600
That was a hard blow! Madam!

167
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:16,720
Damn, she's tough!

168
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:30,080
You look tired. Let's head back.

169
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:33,040
No, I'm still having fun.
I want another round.

170
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,440
Careful, Ms. Nun!

171
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,520
- Ms. Nun!
- Mr. Taiga!

172
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,400
- I've got a cramp!
- Hey!

173
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:05,120
Ms. Nun!

174
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,360
Ms. Nun.

175
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,720
Ms. Nun. Ms. Nun!

176
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:54,760
Ms. Nun.

177
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,960
Thank you so much
for saving me, Mr. Taiga.

178
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,760
If it weren't for you,
I would've been a goner.

179
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:17,600
I didn't save you.

180
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:19,600
Rin did.

181
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:30,720
I'll take you to your room.

182
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,160
Careful.

183
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,520
Let's go.

184
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,520
It's not exactly your style,

185
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:28,320
but you look good.

186
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,120
Ms. Nun gave it to me.

187
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:33,840
Sure.

188
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,440
It's almost not work-appropriate.

189
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:39,960
Then what is?

190
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:45,840
Aren't you a little too judgmental?

191
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,560
When I was little,
my dad would tell me fairy tales.

192
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:02,440
Once there was a poor man,

193
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:05,320
a fisherman named Urashima Taro.

194
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,160
He saved a turtle's life,

195
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:10,720
but he didn't know it was a princess.

196
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,280
So he went from being poor

197
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:23,760
to getting married
and living in an underwater palace.

198
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,360
One day,

199
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,760
he wished to get back to shore.

200
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:32,160
He was very eager, no matter
how the princess would try to stop him.

201
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,600
Once he finally got back,

202
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,720
no one knew him anymore

203
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:40,280
because 300 years had passed.

204
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:46,200
He opened a present the princess gave him
before he would resurface,

205
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:50,080
even after the princess
had kept warning him not to.

206
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,000
Once he opened it,

207
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,120
the young man suddenly

208
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,680
turned into an 80-year-old.

209
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,880
In the end, he died on the beach.

210
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,360
How do you say it in Thai again?

211
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:15,880
Right!

212
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,480
The moral of the story is,

213
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:23,080
disobedience is the beginning of misery

214
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,400
and disaster.

215
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,600
I hope you're not like that.

216
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,360
I trust no one. I only trust my instincts.

217
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:37,240
No matter what you'll have to face?

218
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:40,880
At least it's my choice.

219
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:46,960
I won't argue with you.
You'd give me a headache.

220
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:50,760
Don't worry, I never wanted
to be near you anyway.

221
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:55,040
I'm an employee who wants to keep her job.

222
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,200
Cheers.

223
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:30,360
It's late, Ms. Nun. If you'll excuse me.

224
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:33,280
Wait, Mr. Taiga!

225
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:37,440
You still haven't finished your drink.
Stay here and drink with me.

226
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,720
Good night, Ms. Nun. See you tomorrow.

227
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:44,800
Don't go, Mr. Taiga. Stay with me.

228
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,000
Mr. Taiga!

229
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:58,760
Mr. Taiga, come play in the water with me.

230
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:02,600
Come on! The water's really warm.

231
00:29:58,240 --> 00:30:00,880
I tried to stop her,
but she wouldn't listen.

232
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,080
That's why I had to call you.

233
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,240
Can I have your number?

234
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:17,520
- My number?
- Yeah.

235
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:19,680
So I can check in on her.

236
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,880
She's just drunk.
She'll sober up in no time.

237
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:25,000
It's not like she's badly hurt.

238
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:28,520
Who the hell's drunk?

239
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,040
Mr. Taiga,

240
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:16,320
you're my hero, you know.

241
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:37,240
You can get off of me.
I need to take care of Ms. Nun.

242
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:42,160
We got to know each other better
during this trip.

243
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,080
Is this what they call

244
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:48,440
"intimate"?

245
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:50,720
No.

246
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,920
What did you achieve
by speaking to a designer at the beach?

247
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:45,080
Stop giving people a reason
to talk behind your back.

248
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:51,160
It's only natural
I date someone on my level.

249
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:55,320
In fact, Mr. Taiga's known
at an international level.

250
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:59,080
We're aiming to go global
anyway, aren't we?

251
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:04,720
It's not like I'm taking it out
on lowly people.

252
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:13,160
You sure use your mouth well.

253
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:15,160
That's why the designer likes you.

254
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:19,960
I use my mouth well for work,

255
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:23,160
not just for cheap lust like you do.

256
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,600
What a waste of money and fame.

257
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,720
- Nun!
- Te!

258
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:28,600
- Mom!
- Hey!

259
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,720
Act crazy all you want,
but this is your mother!

260
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,760
Why'd you get in the way, Mom?

261
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:36,880
Dad, relax!

262
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:39,480
- It's okay.
- It's not okay!

263
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:42,480
You keep spoiling them,
never blaming them for anything!

264
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:44,480
Soon, they'll lose all respect for you!

265
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:47,920
What kind of mother are you, Giranun?

266
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,040
Why can't you raise them
to be normal like everyone else?

267
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,480
They're always causing trouble!

268
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,600
I'm rich, yet I can never be happy

269
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:10,880
because I don't have
a good child to show off!

270
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:22,040
Don't cry, Mom. I'll go see Dad.

271
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,159
What are you looking at?

272
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:43,600
If you didn't step in,
Dad wouldn't have yelled at me.

273
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,920
I only want what's best for you.

274
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:48,639
Stop it.

275
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,679
You're always defending me.

276
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:53,400
That's why he thinks
I can never be responsible.

277
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:55,199
When I make any small mistake,

278
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:56,760
he remembers it forever.

279
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:02,240
Yes, I slapped those girls.

280
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,960
What? I just like doing it.

281
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:07,320
Stay still! Got it?

282
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:08,760
Stay still! Stop moving!

283
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:11,480
Let's have some fun, okay?

284
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:31,760
What are you taking pictures for?
What the hell?!

285
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,400
All reporters outside,
please stop taking pictures.

286
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:36,600
Please give my client some privacy.

287
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:42,880
Why are you crying?
You didn't cry like this on the bed!

288
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,040
Te,

289
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:51,320
your dad has high hopes for you.

290
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:56,520
Everything he gave you
was for your own happiness.

291
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,480
If you tarnish my family's name,

292
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,240
you won't get a single penny.

293
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,560
But I've done nothing wrong.

294
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:11,560
- Dad!
- That's enough! Enough!

295
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:13,640
Stop!

296
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:16,360
He's our only son!

297
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:22,000
Are you badly hurt? Are you okay?

298
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:32,160
No one ever asked me what I want.

299
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:43,520
Te…

300
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,760
1089 PEOPLE - 1183

301
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,040
Sun!

302
00:38:32,040 --> 00:38:32,880
Sun,

303
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,960
you were gone because
you were busy with work, right?

304
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:43,520
You have to take care of many people,
like your parents and your sister.

305
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:46,160
I'm back now, Sun.

306
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:47,720
I'll get a job too.

307
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:50,880
I'll help make ends meet.
I'll help you with everything, Sun.

308
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,680
Sun!

309
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,160
She thought I was someone else.

310
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,680
No, I didn't!

311
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:17,520
How could I forget my boyfriend?

312
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,640
Stop it! You're confusing me
with someone else!

313
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:23,040
What a waste of time.

314
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,760
- Let's go.
- Okay.

315
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:07,160
It's been a while, Taiga.

316
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:09,920
- I don't know you.
- But I know you so well.

317
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:12,320
You're not actually Mr. Kenji's son.

318
00:44:14,840 --> 00:44:17,240
What are you, the son
of Blazing Tiger's yakuza boss,

319
00:44:18,120 --> 00:44:19,760
doing at Cosmic Central Group?

320
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:24,080
I…

321
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:26,880
used to know your real parents.

322
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:30,680
And the one who saved you

323
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:32,360
is me.

324
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,240
{\an8}You have to take our kids to Khanin.

325
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:47,240
{\an8}He'll take you all to a hiding place.

326
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:48,080
{\an8}‪-Mom!
‪-No!

327
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,040
{\an8}Dad.

328
00:44:51,720 --> 00:44:52,800
{\an8}Dad, look out!

329
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:57,760
{\an8}If you want Fire Phoenix
to help you, it'll cost you.

330
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:00,320
{\an8}They can take my life.

331
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:03,200
{\an8}We'll hunt them down together.
Even if they're hiding in the shadows,

332
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,520
{\an8}Fire Phoenix needs to be exposed!

333
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:41,040
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

